Here you will find simple example Motion services in various languages.

rot13.js
- Written in JavaScript for Node.
- A quick and dirty Motion service which rot13-"encodes" a message.
- No configuration.

regex.pl
- Written in Perl.
- A basic Motion service which notices regular expression matches in messages.
- Configurable, demonstrating unique and randomized configuration paths.

knights.py
- Written in Python.
- Messages with a "shubbery" property may pass, others are tampered with.
- Configurable, but notice that only one global configuration is used.
- May be allergic to some certain word...
